Today SEVEN POST INVESTMENT OFFICE Filed Its Q3 2015 13F


10/28/2015  by HedgeFundsTracker 
			in 13F Filings 












Share with your friendsYour NameYour EmailRecipient EmailEnter a MessageI read this article and found it very interesting, thought it might be interesting for you. The article is called Today SEVEN POST INVESTMENT OFFICE Filed Its Q3 2015 13F and is was published by Octafinance.com at http://www.octafinance.com/today-seven-post-investment-office-filed-its-q3-2015-13f/243883/.CaptchaSubmit
Seven Post Investment Office Lp 13F Positions
 Seven Post Investment Office Lp just filed its Q3 2015 13F. Dated 28/10/2015, the filing shows the institutional investor has a portfolio value of $113.18 million, representing a decrease of $13.71 million  from the previous quarter when it was $126.89 million. Note: This filling reprents only about 3.02% of Seven Post Investment Office Lp’s assets, which which are listed in the US. 






Portfolio Q32015Market Value:$113,181,000Previous Mkt Value:$126,894,000Chg Mkt Value %:-10.81 % Sentiment:Turnover %:13.29 %




Stocks ActivityNew Purchases:0Additional Purchases:6Sold out:1Reduced:0Top 10 Holdings %:100.01%






Based on $3.75 billion in assets under management, Seven Post Investment Office Lp’s equity exposure is only 3.02% of assets. Please also note that we can’t know the Seven Post Investment Office Lp’s shorts and net exposure. 






Top 5 New Buys-----




13F Sector AllocationFinance85 %Transports15 %---






Increased Positions
 The institutional investor didn’t report any upped stakes in this quarter. 
Top 3 Holdings
Vanguard Intl Equity Index F (VWO), Alexander & Baldwin Inc New (ALEX) and Spdr S&P 500 Etf Tr (SPY) made up the majority of Seven Post Investment Office Lp’s total US long portfolio in this quarter. These positions were top 3 and constitute 84.88% of Seven Post Investment Office Lp’s US-listed securities. 

 The chart above provides a snapshot of Seven Post Investment Office Lp’s top 10 US-listed holdings in this quarter. 
 Sectors Share
Seven Post Investment Office Lp upped the finance sector from 84 % to 85 %. The fund slashed the Transports sector stakes by 15 %. 
So these are Q3 2015 fund’s sector weights now: finance 85 % for $96.20 million and transports 15 % for $16.98 million.
Important Position Changes
Top 10 Q3 2015 Sold Out Completely: Ishares Inc (IEMG).
